description: This unit is located in the La Voyageur building, on Church St. Due to the location, the harbour is only visible from the front bay windows. This unit is fully enclosed and does not offer a courtyard. There is a bench-top cooker in the kitchenette.
host_about:
With your comfortable waterfront apartment home base secure, it is time to explore the outer bays of the Banks Peninsula, or around the harbour itself. The choices are many, with kayaking, sailing, paddle boarding and boating all an option. Perhaps take a walk along one of the many posted trails, or ride a bike, or simply stroll along the foreshore for a spot of shopping or people watching. The Akaroa Village Inn offers great waterfront accommodation for families or couples looking for that perfect holiday or weekend getaway.
Akaroa Village Inn provides some of the most comfortable waterfront apartments and family friendly motel type suites on the Banks Peninsula. With a range of designs and layouts, many of the apartments offer spectacular views of the magnificent Akaroa harbour, and all are centrally located close to major attractions, restaurants, bars, and shopping.

We feel honoured and humbled by the opportunity to present this magical slice of pure New Zealand to the world so that others may come to love this special place as much as we do. We feel our responsibility is to provide an experience which enables each of us and our communities to flourish based upon principles of love, integrity and respect. We are a family business with a social conscience.

Akaroa Accommodation at the Village Inn has stunning sea views, with most of the upstairs or downstairs units having two bedrooms. Renowned for quality, comfort, style, and convenience, Akaroa Village Accommodation is across the road from many Akaroa cafes and restaurants and is only 90 minutes from Christchurch.

Read a bit of Akaroa history
The Village Inn in Akaroa boasts some of the most stylish and comfortable waterfront apartment and motel type suites on the Banks Peninsula. Each apartment comes with tea, coffee and toast making facilities, right through to a full-size kitchen in many, spacious living area, WiFi service, Sky and Freeview television, on-site guest laundry facilities, and private parking. Some apartments also include a spa bath. Our friendly, helpful staff will go out of their way to ensure you can make the most of your precious time in Akaroa.
No matter the occasion, if you are looking for something special with comfort, convenience, and style, then look no further than the Akaroa Village Inn. Our quality shines through, and customer service which goes the extra mile, to deliver a unique guest experience which is responsive to you. We can seamlessly bring together all the details for a picture-perfect honeymoon, anniversary or special occasion, or even those looking to explore the local flora, fauna and history of the Banks Peninsula.

host_about:
Twizel Holiday Homes has been connecting folk like you with holiday houses in the Twizel area of New Zealand for more than 10 years. Ever since I came to Twizel I've been  constantly impressed by the landscape which has the natural results of tectonic plates at work always on display. Rugged mountains softened by snow in winter but bare and beautiful in summer and autumn. Retreating glaciers have gifted us 5 lakes and a landscape that’s a feast for the eyes at any time of the year. As I drive around the corner, going home, there is Mt Cook looking like its just at the end of the street. 
When I am not in the office I enjoy the finer things in life that are being produced locally. Wine, beer, cheese and the best fresh water farmed salmon in the world are produced here.
A suggestion! After driving around the South island for a few days take a little time in one of our houses to get the laundry done and stretch your legs on a walk by the river or further afield. Recall what it was like on a bike when you were younger by riding one of the many local tracks or part of the Alps to Ocean Cycle Trail. 
Some of the biggest trout caught in the world have been caught here recently and some are waiting to be caught? Are they waiting for you?
The night sky in Twizel is as spectacular as anywhere else in the Mackenzie Basin. In winter our view into the Milky Way is even better than it is in summer. You can choose a house on the edge of town or in the countryside and sit on the patio and gaze at the stars, maybe even see the space station go by. 
We are pleased to offer you  a choice of houses from the modest to the splendid, all well equipped and very clean. These are Kiwis' holiday homes. The owners enjoy sharing them with you as we do.
My tip as a local? Keep your camera handy! The magic moments formed on the landscape by the combination of foliage, the sun, water and clouds only lasts minutes.  Your memories will stay but if you want to show others then capture them when you see them.

name: 11 Pekanga Drive Fox Glacier
description: Welcome to your unique home-away-from-home, nestled in the heart of Fox Glacier, on the majestic West Coast of New Zealand. Our property combines the charm and history of The Ole Woolshed - a recently renovated four-bedroom home with a rich history, with the cosy and private Shearers Rest - A charming 2-bedroom abode, offering a whole-property rental experience that accommodates families, large groups and those seeking a getaway amidst nature's splendor.
host_about:
Hello, I'm Eunice, Australian born living in NZ.
I Married my husband Michael (Kiwi) 45 years ago.
Our House is located 110m West of Fox Glacier township & is run by third generation farming and tourism family (Eunice & Michael Sullivan) one of the original founding families of Fox Glacier..
We have 3 children, 3 grandchildren and 2 cats.
My interests are gardening, cooking. My main hobby is patchwork & quilting. Our bedrooms are all set up beautifully with my own homemade quilts.
My husband Michaels hobby is classic trucks and other vehicles. He has 2 restored International Trucks, 2 Motorbikes, 1 MGB car.
I have been hosting for 24 years, and still enjoy meeting people from all over the world!

Fox Glacier lies within the breathtaking World Heritage Listed Area on the South Island's West Coast. The glaciers are certainly some of the most attractive tourist destinations in the South Island of New Zealand and a must-see for all visitors to the West Coast. 
Under the watchful gaze of both Mount Cook and Mount Tasman, the two tallest mountains in Oceania, Fox Glacier snakes for almost 14 kilometres down the mountains. A pristine natural wilderness surrounds both the glacier and the township and provides a host of different scenic views as well as trails and bushwalks.
For the adventurous, a range of guided tours offer glacier walking, heli-hiking, ice climbing and mountaineering courses. Or just sit and relax in one of the many cafes or by taking a stroll around beautiful Lake Matheson, the famous mirror lake located in Fox Glacier itself. 
The Nightlife is literally glowing with the Glow-Worm Bush Walk, a nice 20 min stroll just on the edge of the town.
We hope you enjoy your time in Fox Glacier and look forward to seeing you soon!
We do not reside at the House

We love Winnies Gourmet Pizza Bar – its indulgent and delicious and is great for almost all demographics for lunch or dinner but be aware that after 9pm it gets a very young crowd. Try the Montonara! Another one of our favourites is Madam Woo which is Vietnamese Street food style cuisine.
